    {
      "id": "9119f1793079ca21967cb7235b188e3a56cd8a74",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-12-23 23:59:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThe patch itself looks ok, but my comment on patch #1 about adding a test case was missed. As it stands, we don't have any idea if this code works or if it will continue to work. \n\nIt would be worthwhile to grep lustre/tests/*.sh to see if there tests accessing brw_stats that are disabled for ZFS (I don't see how they could be working right now), or listed in ALWAYS_EXCEPT.\n\nFailing that, adding some new tests to verify the contents of brw_stats would be good. Something simple like zeroing the stats, doing some amount of large writes and syncing, then verifying the writes show up on the proper OSD's brw_stats. This could be combined with some existing test already doing a large amount of IO to reduce test time if that was considered important. It should also be skipped if the OST is running an older version of Lustre (e.g. brw_stats file is missing).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "6ed9c53577b7bc2090e7902b55ea5a9f87f34196",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-12-24 00:00:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nPS: I'd rather get this working than hold it up, so no -1 for the patch due to the missing test, but it would be good to test this code as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
